Name:LRFSV: Xiyue Fire Support Vehicle
Description:LRFSV: [Side] Soviet Union - Eastern United Front
  [Unit Type] T3 Anti‑Armor Unit
  [Armor] Heavy
  [Weapons]
    [Xiyue Missile]
    - Damage Type: Armor‑Piercing (AP)
    - Anti‑armor
    - Releases a [Mini Terror Drone] at the target (self‑detonates actively)
    - Alternates with [EMP Missile]
    - Used only in Form I
    [EMP Missile]
    - Damage Type: High Explosive (HE)
    - Anti‑armor, anti‑building
    - Reduces enemy movement and attack speed by 40%
    - Used only in Form I
    [Electronic Countermeasure System]
    - Deploys full‑jamming ECM, losing mobility
    - Reduces speed and attack of all armored units in range by 60% (friend and foe)
    - Provides protection for all friendly units in range (15% chance to evade damage, non‑stackable)
    - Used only in Form II
  [Special Properties]
  - Immune to all crushing
  - Auto‑repairs
  - Can be permanently upgraded by support superweapon [Xiyue: Electronic Module Upgrade]
  - Limited to 9 (shared before/after upgrade)
  - Can enter Tank Bunkers
  - Immune to gravity effects
  - Deploy to switch between Form I and Form II
Name:LRFSVUPSP: Xiyue: Electronic Module Upgrade
Description:LRFSVUPSP: Upgrades all [Xiyue Fire Support Vehicles] on the field
  Grants the following enhancements:
  Increased range for [Xiyue Missile] and [EMP Missile]
  [EMP Missile] now inflicts a 2‑second EMP effect on hit enemy armored units or buildings; increased damage to buildings
  [Electronic Countermeasure System] is fully upgraded, no longer affects friendlies,
  and increases attack speed of friendly [Qilin Breaker Tanks] in range by 50%
Name:LRFSVUP: Xiyue Fire Support Vehicle (Upgraded)
