TXT_SWITCH_NOMOVE: Toggle No‑Move Mode
TXT_SWITCH_NOMOVE_DESC: When the unit's intended action differs from the mouse behavior and would cause movement toward the target, replace it with hold position.
TXT_DISTR_SPREAD: Target Distribution Range
TXT_DISTR_SPREAD_DESC: In target distribution mode, range 0 uses default behavior; hotkeys adjust range to 4, 8, or 16 cells. Selected units will then evenly distribute targets within range. Distribution only occurs if the intended action matches the mouse behavior, otherwise defaults to original behavior (does not affect air units). An indicator ring shows the range. You can also adjust range with mouse wheel while holding the toggle hotkey.
TXT_DISTR_FILTER: Target Distribution Filter
TXT_DISTR_FILTER_DESC: Mode `None` uses default behavior; if range is not 0, a green ring appears. Hotkeys cycle modes:
  - `Like` – targets of the same armor type (blue ring)
  - `Type` – targets of the same type (infantry, vehicle, building) (yellow ring)
  - `Name` – targets of the same name or `GroupAs` name (red ring)
TXT_DISTR_HOLDDOWN: Target Distribution Mode Toggle
TXT_DISTR_HOLDDOWN_DESC: Hold this hotkey and use mouse wheel to adjust distribution range
MSG:DistributionModeOn: Target Distribution Mode: On
MSG:DistributionModeOff: Target Distribution Mode: Off
